    "body": "This is due to https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/9e8cc00b733a505c2815b58d94315298371579cb/p2p/server.go#L914:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\t\tgo func() {\r\n\t\t\tsrv.SetupConn(fd, inboundConn, nil)\r\n\t\t\tslots <- struct{}{}\r\n\t\t}()\r\n```\r\nWe start a goroutine which does not add to the `wg`, and thus it can print a log message even after the server has been stopped\r\n",
